result.execSummary:
The defendant Jason A. Scheel was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Child Enticement-Sexual Contact, a class D felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.07(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Probation may be transferred to Wood County.

miscConds.notes: Maintain GFE in FTE/schooling or combination of the two.  When not fully engaged, complete 5 hours of community service per week.

No contact with anyone under the age of 18 without prior agent approval and without chaperone.  Allowed to have contact with own minor children and able to attend child's school events with other adults present.   

No unauthorized use of internet unless approved by agent.

If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.  

A copy of the police report has been electronically sent to the probation office.

Complete any assessment, treatment, counseling deemed necessary by agent.  Successfully complete sex offender treatment and comply with sex offender registry.    DNA sample.

timeConds.notes: Jail may be served in Clark County.  Jail may be with huber release for work/treatment if meets jail criteria.
